===Etymology===
Since metals are typically associated with color, the word is probably related to {{och-l|彤|red}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

The word "copper" occurs in some Southeast Asian languages with initial ''l-'' ({{zh-ref|Sagart, 1999}}). Examples include {{cog|za|luengz}}, {{cog|pcc|luangz}} and {{cog|bwx|loŋ²}}, which are early loans from Chinese.

{{cog|bo|དོང་ཙེ||Chinese copper coin}} was borrowed from {{cog|zh|-}} {{zh-l|銅子}}.

